<paragraph id="6F14D266FFE91E28FF4BF96526C1F91E" blockId="4.[200,1694,1633,2240]" box="[204,749,1692,1724]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="A8ABA9E5FFE91E28FF4BF9652619F91E" authority="Bezzi" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1908" box="[204,565,1692,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFE91E28FF4BF96525F6F91E" box="[204,474,1693,1724]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Laphria serpentina</emphasis>
Bezzi
</taxonomicName>
, [908 p. 378
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F14D266FFE91E28FF74F92827B8F819" blockId="4.[200,1694,1633,2240]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Oldroyd (1974) doubtfully assigned specimens from Malawi, Mozambique and South Africa to this species. I here present an illustration of the male genital bulb drawn from the only specimen available to me (
<figureCitation id="F790CEE3FFE91E28FB82F8C92047F8F5" box="[1029,1131,1841,1879]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[210,272,2476,2508]" captionTargetBox="[255,1619,337,2380]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5. Choerades species; dorsal aspect of cr genital bulb 1. C. aureopilosa (Ricardo). 2. C. bella (Loew). 3. C. jlavipes (Weidemann). 4. C. nigrescens (Ricardo) 5. C. serpentina (Bezzi)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472447/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Fused gonopodal setae curved in an S-like manner with distal points pointing outwards. Aedeagal structure very well developed and extended posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F14D266FFE91E28FF74F83E21B9F7ED" blockId="4.[200,1694,1633,2240]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
The male terminalia of the specimen studied are quite distinctive and there should be no trouble recognizing this species. A comparison with the type specimens should reveal whether southern African specimens are indeed 
<taxonomicName id="A8ABA9E5FFE91E28FB2EF7D221BCF7ED" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1908" box="[1193,1424,2090,2127]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFE91E28FB2EF7D220EAF7EC" box="[1193,1222,2090,2126]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFE91E28FB67F7D221B9F7ED" box="[1248,1429,2090,2127]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">serpentina.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
